{{afc comment|Wikidata entry [[d:Q840081]] Wikidata name: 2nd day of the 11th month in the Chinese calendar [[User:Immanuelle|Immanuelle]] ([[User talk:Immanuelle|talk]]) 08:37, 11 June 2025 (UTC)}} {{Not to be confused with|November 2|qq=November 2}}[[Category:Days of the Japanese Lunisolar Calendar]]<!--why is this category always showing up as 347 members?--> {{afc comment|1=This article as with the other date articles is relatively limited in scope to Japan. Reviewing the translation of this is good and also adding content translated from Chinese and Korean wikipedias will also be good. Both wikipedias are also relatively centered around their own countries for their Lunisolar calendar dates[[User:Immanuelle|Immanuelle]] ([[User talk:Immanuelle|talk]]) 00:16, 28 April 2025 (UTC)}} {{Globalize|article|Japan|date=April 2025}} {{Expand Chinese|1=十一月初二|topic=hist|date=April 2025}} {{Expand Korean|1=음력 11월 2일|topic=hist|date=April 2025}} {{Lunisolar November|qq=}} '''November 2''' is the 2nd day of the month {{ill|November (Lunisolar)|ja|11月 (旧暦)|lt=November (Shimotsuki)|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/November (Lunisolar)|qq=}}, the 11th month of the traditional {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|13=User:Immanuelle/Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=}}. Its {{ill|Rokuyō|ja|六曜|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Rokuyō|qq=}} day is {{ill|Shakkō|ja|赤口|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shakkō|qq=|1=Shakkō|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q11635368}}.
== Events == * In the 4th year of the Meiji era (Gregorian calendar [[:en:1871|1871]] [[:en:December 13|December 13]]), the territories of Akita Prefecture were established through the merger of [[久保田藩|Kubota Domain]] (labeled as Akita), Iwasaki, Honjō, Kameda, and Yajima into [[:en:秋田県|秋田県]]. * In the 4th year of the Meiji era (Gregorian calendar [[:en:1871|1871]] [[:en:December 13|December 13]]), Sendai, Ishinomaki, and Kakuda were merged to form Sendai Prefecture, establishing the current boundaries of [[:en:宮城県|宮城県]] (Miyagi Prefecture).
== Births == * [[:en:Shōō (Kamakura period)|Shōō]] 1st year (Julian calendar [[:en:1288|1288]] [[:en:November 26|November 26]]) – Emperor Go-Daigo, the 96th Emperor of Japan (d. [[:en:1339|1339]]). * [[:en:Tenpō|Tenpō]] 8th year (Gregorian calendar [[:en:1837|1837]] [[:en:December 9|December 9]]) – Kabayama Sashinori, a Satsuma Domain samurai and politician (d. [[:en:1922|1922]]). * [[:en:Keiō|Keiō]] 1st year (Gregorian calendar [[:en:1865|1865]] [[:en:December 19|December 19]]) – Itō Satoki, a Japanese woman who contributed to emigration to North America (d. [[:en:1950|1950]]). * [[:en:Meiji era|Meiji]] 5th year (Gregorian calendar [[:en:1872|1872]] [[:en:December 2|December 2]]) – Takejima Hagoromo, a scholar of national literature (d. [[:en:1967|1967]]). * In the Gregorian year [[:en:1941|1941]] (December 19), Lee Myung-bak, the 17th President of the Republic of Korea, was born.
== Deaths == * [[:en:Kōji (Muromachi period)|Kōji]] 3rd year (Julian calendar [[:en:1557|1557]] [[:en:November 22|November 22]]) – Oda Nobuyuki, a military commander ({{ill|Busho (Rank)|ja|武将|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Busho (Rank)|qq=|1=military commander|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q11545923}}) and the younger brother of Oda Nobunaga. * [[正徳 (日本)|Shōtoku]] 4th year (Gregorian calendar [[:en:1714|1714]] [[:en:December 8|December 8]]) – Yanagisawa Yoshiyasu, a Rōjū of the Tokugawa shogunate (born [[:en:1658|1658]]). * [[:en:Bunka|Bunka]] 10th year (leap month) (Gregorian calendar [[:en:1813|1813]] [[:en:December 24|December 24]]) – Emperor Go-Sakuramachi, the 117th Emperor of Japan (born [[:en:1740|1740]]). * [[:en:Bunsei|Bunsei]] 4th year (Gregorian calendar [[:en:1821|1821]] [[:en:November 26|November 26]]) – Kinoshita Yukifumi, a waka poet (born [[:en:1779|1779]]).
